Release Notes:

The Asteroids Galaxy Tour is a Danish alternative band
consisting of Mette Lindberg, Lars Iversen, Miloud Carl Sabri,
Sven Meinilid, Mads Brinch Nielsen, and Jasper Einegaard.
Iversen is their primary songwriter, and often uses small
samples to create their tracks. Their debut single, "The Sun
Ain't Shining No More", was released on September 15, 2008.
The band has become known for its song "Around the Bend",
which was used in an Apple iPod Touch commercial starting in
September 2008, and released as a single in October. An EP
version featuring two new tracks was released in November.

The Asteroids Galaxy Tour's debut album is set to release in
April 2009. The band confirmed that the title of their debut
album will be 'Fruit'. This will include their songs "The Sun
Ain't Shining No More" and their famous iPod advert song
"Around The Bend". The official date is yet to be announced,
the band is likely to announce the official day on their
myspace page where they have previously announced all other
information.
